commands are the way we set and retrieve a string value. Note that
will replace any existing value already stored into the key, in the case that the key already exists, even if the key is associated with a non-string value. So
Values can be strings (including binary data) of every kind, for instance you can store a jpeg image inside a value. A value can't be bigger than 512 MB.
command has interesting options that are provided as additional arguments. For example, I may ask
to fail if the key already exists, or the opposite, that it only succeed if the key already exists:
Conditional SET operations: Use NX and XX options to control key existence when you need atomic compare-and-set behavior
There are a number of other commands for operating on strings. For example the
